        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 3:52PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 352 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Cooksville, or 18 miles northeast of De Kalb, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Panola and Geiger.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
